comments: Morris (WAS) makes clean contact with the ball to dislodge it from Murray's (ATL) possession.
Young (ATL) initiates contact with Morris' (WAS) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Porzingis (WAS) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Kuzma (WAS) never fully clears the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.

Kuzma (WAS) establishes himself in a legal guarding position outside of the restricted area and is dislodged from his position by Hunter (ATL).  After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor is confirmed.
Hunter (ATL) is moving alongside Beal's (WAS) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Collins (ATL) wraps Porzingis (WAS), which affects his ability to get to the pass in the post.
Beal (WAS) commits a take foul on Young (ATL).
ATL does not signal for a timeout within five seconds of the ball being at Hunter's (ATL) disposal during the throw-in.
Capela (ATL) is established in a screening position in Beal's (WAS) path and absorbs the contact.  The initial contact causes him to step backwards and marginal contact occurs with Beal.
Hunter (ATL) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds and WAS should be given possession.
Wright (WAS) intentionally kicks the ball during the throw-in.

call_type: Turnover: Lost Ball Out of Bounds
comments: Beal (WAS) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds and ATL should retain possession.
Morris (WAS) commits a take foul on Murray (ATL).
Hunter (ATL) retreats and jumps backwards, absorbing the contact initiated by Beal (WAS) during the driving shot attempt.
Beal (WAS) initiates foot to foot contact with Murray (ATL) and trips him affecting his SQBR.
Porzingis (WAS) commits a take foul on Hunter (ATL).
